<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1902-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1902-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Dr.
                                    <persName type="to">von Holleben</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1902-05-20"><hi rend="italic">May 20,
                                1902</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Excellency</hi>: I have pleasure in saying
                            that, at my request the Secretary of the Navy has instructed the
                            commander of the <hi rend="italic">Machias</hi> to render such
                            protection as he may find in his power to German interests at Bocas del
                            Toro, in case the German consul in Colon should address such a request
                            to the representatives of the United States a Colon and Bocas del
                            Toro.</p>
                        <p>Very sincerely, yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay</hi>.</signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>